                <h3>Quang Noodles</h3>
                <p>
                    Quang noodle dish is a famous specialty of Quang Nam province, but it is a popular national dish throughout the country. Ingredients to make a bowl of Quang noodles include: yellow noodles, rice paper, peanuts, crispy roasted pork and marinated with thick turmeric-yellow broth.
                </p>
                <img src="https://go2joy.s3.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/14172249/mon-an-viet-nam.jpg" alt="">
                <h3>Pho</h3>
                <p>
                    Vietnam has long been famous for its traditional pho. This is a dish cooked very elaborately with the broth being stewed from beef bones, cinnamon, anise, ... for 6-8 hours, so that the broth will be naturally sweet. The combination with soft noodle soup, fresh vegetables also brings a dish suitable for all ages.
                </p>
                <img src="https://go2joy.s3.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/14172313/do-an-viet-nam.jpg" alt="">
                <h3>Spring rolls</h3>
                <p>
                    Goi cuon is currently the perfect light dish and has a rich Vietnamese flavor with simple ingredients such as vermicelli, vermicelli, shrimp, pork and greens, all wrapped up inside a layer. Thin and chewy rice paper so that you can eat it.
                </p>
                <img src="https://go2joy.s3.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/14172335/cac-mon-an-viet-nam.jpg" alt="">
                <h3>Bun cha</h3>
                <p>
                    Bun Cha is a typical dish of Hanoi capital. Thanks to the delicious taste that is hard to come by, bun cha is gradually introduced into provinces and cities across Vietnam. The dish is a combination of grilled meat, rice vermicelli, fish sauce and many other accompanying spices such as herbsâ€¦
                </p>
                <img src="https://go2joy.s3.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/14172430/mon-an-viet.jpg" alt="">
                <h3>Bun mam</h3>
                <p>
                    Bun mam is one of the specialties of the southwestern region of Vietnam. This delicious Vietnamese dish is often modified by many locals with different ingredients. But the main indispensable ingredient is Linh fish sauce. The more delicious the fish sauce, the more delicious the flavor of bun mam is.
                </p>
                <img src="https://go2joy.s3.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/14172517/cac-mon-an-noi-tieng-o-viet-nam.jpg" alt="">
                <h3>Com tam</h3>
                <p>
                    Com tam is an extremely popular lunch in Saigon, not only popular at noon but also in the morning and evening. With a plate of com tam served with grilled pork or pork ribs, adding pork belly with onions, served with pickles and some spices, the dish is irresistible.
                </p>
